==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ophthalmoscopy
<hw>Oph`thal*mos"co*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ophthalmoscopie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A branch of
physiognomy which deduces the knowledge of a person's temper and
character from the appearance of the eyes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Examination of the eye with the
ophthalmoscope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1006 --></p>

<p><ent>Ophthalmy</ent>⟦br⟧
